            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best Practices for Production Deployment"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optimize performance by batching requests where possible and setting timeouts to 30 seconds. Use exponential backoff for retries on HTTP 429 or 5xx errors. Cache frequent responses with a TTL of 5 minutes to reduce load. Monitor rate limits via the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "X-RateLimit-Remaining",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " header and adjust concurrency accordingly."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Monitoring and Troubleshooting"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integrate logging with tools like Prometheus or ELK stack to track metrics such as request latency and error rates. Common issues include authentication failures (HTTP 401) and payload size limits (HTTP 413). For debugging, enable verbose logging in non-production environments and use the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "/v1/logs",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " endpoint to retrieve error details."
